It is recommended that if you have not made extensive
customizations, you NOT convert your old configuration.
Starting from scratch will help familiarize you with the new
features, and will help prevent conflicts with outdated
keymapping, etc.

To convert your old configuration, you must first have installed
version 7.0 in a DIFFERENT directory than the previous version.
If you answered the install prompt for updating a previous
version then you will have been taken to convert directly.  The
macro CONV_700 is what is run to perform the conversion.  If you
manually run CONV_700, it really should be done BEFORE
installing VCS support, but AFTER the Wordstar or Brief
emulations.

If you are converting a network version, with multiple user
setups, you need to take special precautions.  CONV_700 MUST
ONLY BE RUN BY SOMEONE WITH SUPERVISOR RIGHTS!  Also, it only
needs to be run only once.  Individual users need not, and
should not run CONV_700.

NOTE: The CONV_700 macro is no longer installed by Module
Installation.  It is done automatically during the initial
installation.

Press <F10> to proceed.

Proceed through Module Installation.  Install all of your
desired options EXCEPT VCS support.
≥
¿ƒƒƒƒƒ DO NOT INSTALL VCS SUPPORT UNTIL AFTER THE CONVERSION
	IS COMPLETE!

After you have completed Module Installation, you will be taken
directly to the 7.0 conversion utility.  After the conversion is
complete, you may go back to Module Installation and install VCS
support.

Press <F10> to proceed.
